title: NYC Special Purpose Districts With Subdistricts (Zoning)
name: NYC Special Purpose Districts With Subdistricts (Zoning)
description:
Polygon features representing the Special Purpose Districts and their associated sub-districts. The main district designation is indicated in the SDNAME attribute. The abbreviation as shown on the zoning map is indicated in the SDLBL attribute. Sub-districts and divisions within sub-districts are indicated in the SUBDIST and SUBSUB attributes respectively.

This feature class was formerly known as NYSP. As of September 2010, NYSP will contain only the special purpose district boundary and no subdistricts. NYSP_SD will contain the main special purpose district boundaries and the internal subdistricts. Both NYSP and NYSP_SD will be included with the monthly updates to the downloadable zoning GIS features.
